"""5-method registration comparison using watershed HCR binarisation.

Protocol (revised 2026-04-26):
  1. Run M1 (rigid, FFT-NCC θ-sweep) on the FULL HCR canvas.
  2. Crop HCR (and the warped CZ) to the bounding box of the M1
     mapping, expanded by 15 % on each side.
  3. Run M2-M5 on the cropped frame.
  4. NCC is ALWAYS computed binary-vs-binary on the cropped frame
     (warped CZ binarised at > 0.5).

Methods (all initialised by the same rigid stage):
  M1 rigid               — translation + rotation only.
  M2 rigid + affine      — 4-DOF similarity, scale ±15 %, θ ±15°.
  M3 rigid + coarse Bspl — M2 affine then coarse BSpline (mesh=6,
                           multi-resolution, displacement-field
                           smoothed σ=4 px).
  M4 rigid + PWR (binary)— Suite2p-style piecewise rigid 4×4 grid
                           on binary masks.
  M5 rigid + PWR (intens)— same 4×4 PWR but block NCC computed in
                           intensity domain (HCR 488 raw vs blurred
                           CZ binary); DF then applied to the
                           binary rigid-warp.

Outputs:
  • figures/compare_methods_watershed_{sid}.png — 2×3 panel per subject
  • figures/compare_methods_watershed_summary.png — bar chart
  • compare_methods_watershed_summary.json
"""
